				'<p>Patra Patri &#8211; A cute and adorable visual enactment play or as said by Vijay Kenkre &#8211; \u201c\u090f\u0915 \u0926\u094d\u0930\u0942\u0915 \u0905\u0935\u093f\u0937\u094d\u0915\u093e\u0930\u201d, is basically a sweet conversation of handwritten letters between two characters in their 50s &#038; 60s &#8211; Tatyasaheb and Madhavrao. The character of Tatyasaheb is played by our beloved and lovely Dilip Prabhavalkar and the character of Madhavrao is played by Vijay Kenkre. </p>\n<p>Fortunately, I had the chance to watch one of their first opening shows, and I must say, I was impressed by how soothing and sweet the entire format of the play was set and delivered. Therefore, this is my short review blog of Patra Patri.</p>\n',
