			rendered:
				'\n<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Why is JAI BHIM Special?</strong></h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>JAI BHIM &#8211; The Heartbreaking Story of a Tribal Man Who Was Falsely Accused of Robbery</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>JAI BHIM is a stirring and moving movie about social justice and injustice in contemporary India. Poor tribal guy Rajakannu is wrongly charged with robbery and escapes from police custody. A fearless activist lawyer named Adv. Chandru battles for justice and looks for the facts surrounding Rajakannu&#8217;s disappearance.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Inspiring Performance by Suriya as a Brave Activist-Lawyer</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The film is a heart-wrenching tale of how the marginalised and oppressed are often targeted and mistreated by those in positions of power. The performance by Surya is truly inspiring, as he risks everything to stand up for what he believes in and seek justice for Rajakannu.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>A Must-Watch on Amazon Prime for those Seeking Social Change</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Overall, JAI BHIM is a must-watch for those seeking to bring about social change and make a difference in the world. It is available now on Amazon Prime and is definitely worth a watch for anyone interested in these important themes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Cast &#8211;&nbsp;</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Adv. Chandru is played by Suriya.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Sengeni Rajakannu played by Lijomol Jose.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Mythra is played by Rjisha Vijayan.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Rajakannu played by K.Manikandan</li>\n\n\n\n<li>IG Perumalswamy played by Prakash Raj.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The amazing group of JAI BHIM performers gives each of their characters depth and heart. Suriya, who plays the role of Adv. Chandru, provides a strong performance as the activist attorney seeking justice. His commitment to finding the truth and fighting for the underprivileged is very admirable.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Actor K. Manikandan portrays the tribal man mistakenly charged with robbery, Rajakannu. He gives a touching and moving performance as he battles to establish his innocence and cope with the unfairness he encounters.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>My Key Takeaways From The Movie</strong> </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>&#8220;Jai Bhim&#8221; is a powerful film available on <a href="https://www.primevideo.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" title="Amazon Prime">Amazon Prime</a> that tackles the issue of caste discrimination and violence in India. Through its poignant storytelling, the film offers valuable lessons about the harmful effects of discrimination and the importance of standing up for justice.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are some key points to consider about the lessons learned from &#8220;Jai Bhim\u201d</p>\n\n\n\n<ol>\n<li>The film highlights the ongoing issue of caste discrimination in India, which has a long and complex history. Despite efforts to combat it, discrimination based on caste remains a pervasive problem in Indian society, particularly for those in the lower castes.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<ol start="2">\n<li>&#8220;Jai Bhim&#8221; demonstrates the devastating consequences of discrimination, including violence, poverty, and social exclusion. The film follows the story of a Dalit man brutally beaten by upper-caste police officers, highlighting the institutionalised nature of caste discrimination.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<ol start="3">\n<li>The film also shows the importance of resistance and resilience in the face of injustice. The main character, despite facing immense adversity, remains committed to fighting for his rights and those of his community.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<ol start="4">\n<li>&nbsp;&#8220;Jai Bhim&#8221; encourages viewers to stand up against discrimination and work towards creating a more equal and just society. It is a powerful reminder of the need for collective action and solidarity in the face of injustice.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<p>In conclusion, &#8220;Jai Bhim&#8221; is a thought-provoking film that offers valuable lessons about the harmful effects of discrimination and the importance of standing up for justice. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>By highlighting the ongoing issue of caste discrimination in India and the resilience of those affected by it, the film encourages viewers to take action and work towards a more equal society.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Written By &#8211; Harsh Gupta</p>\n\n\n\n<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity"/>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Also Read &#8211; </strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://veryfirsttale.in/2022/12/the-best-marathi-natak-aamne-samne-a-blockbuster-hit-with-modern-story-all-presented-in-a-hilarious-way/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" title="The Best Marathi Natak \u2013 Aamne Samne \u2013 A Blockbuster Hit With Modern Story \u2013 All Presented in A Hilarious Way">The Best Marathi Natak \u2013 Aamne Samne \u2013 A Blockbuster Hit With Modern Story \u2013 All Presented in A Hilarious Way</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://veryfirsttale.in/2023/01/rocky-balboa-the-unforgettable-tale-of-a-true-underdog/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" title="Rocky Balboa: The Unforgettable Tale of a True Underdog!">Rocky Balboa: The Unforgettable Tale of a True Underdog!</a></p>\n',
