				'<p>Indian drivers can now rent a car in Poland with their Indian driving license by booking with car rental companies like Carwiz and Discover Cars. Discover Cars offers competitive prices, 24/7 support, free cancellations, and no hidden costs in over 145 countries and 10,000 locations. Renting a car in Poland can cost on average INR 3,900 to INR 30,000 per day, depending on the type of car, and it is recommended to purchase the full insurance package directly from the car operator to avoid a larger security deposit. An international driving permit (IDP) is required to rent a car in Poland, which can be obtained through the Saarthi Parivahan website for a fee of INR 1000. Google Maps is sufficient for navigation, but it is important to have all necessary documents, including the IDP, Indian driving license, and passport, when picking up the rental car.</p>\n',
